<br>
In Japanese, no prefix to a name is used. Surnames are used as suffixes to names like below.<br>
<br>
Name + shi, Name + sama, Name + san, Name + chan, etc.:<br>
<br>
Bush sama = Mr. President Bush or the like when addressing the superior<br>
Bush shi = President Bush or the like when reffering to a person<br>
Kazuya san = Kazuya: applicable to any cases as the most common usage<br>
Kazuya chan = (My friend Kazuya); for addressing or reffering to a close friend, or among close firends, one's junior, etc. with deep affection or friendship<br>
<br>
